description: Bright, art-filled, spacious loft in prime Williamsburg, Brooklyn (2 blocks from subway, 1 stop from Manhattan); King-size bed, walk-in shower, sit-n-spin tub, full bedroom, living room, kitchen, dining area, 12 foot high ceiling. Near lots of delicious eateries, cafes, music venues, nightlife, parks, yet on a quiet street. Perfect for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers. Classic artist loft in converted brick warehouse building. Possible use of private roof deck. 1st Flr-Eu, 2nd Fl-US

hosts.about: My husband and I have a contemporary art gallery in NYC. My husband is also an artist who moved from California to Williamsburg, Brooklyn in the late 1980s, when the art community was really developing there. I worked in design in NYC, studied creative writing and cultural anthropology, and now run the gallery with him. Our building is a converted warehouse building, very typical of NYC artists' lofts. When not involved in art and writing I like to read, run, ride my bike, and travel. We split our time between Brooklyn and PA.
